{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775823066644,"sessionID":"ses_288b6174dffe0vBM04EEI0J8t9","part":{"id":"prt_d774a02a2001dvaKRSA5tS6RFB","messageID":"msg_d7749f4940013hMWV3EZsKbroF","sessionID":"ses_288b6174dffe0vBM04EEI0J8t9","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_d5504b5e7a204aabb54f4ce8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore workloadmanager module","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the codebase at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n\n1. The structure of pkg/workloadmanager - find all Go files, understand the module's purpose\n2. Any existing GC (garbage collection) or cleanup mechanisms\n3. How sandboxes/workloads are created, tracked, and deleted\n4. Any existing timer-based or cron-based mechanisms\n5. The AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD types and their lifecycle\n6. Any existing proposals or design docs in the repo\n7. The overall project structure\n\nReturn:\n- Full directory listing of pkg/workloadmanager\n- Key types and interfaces found\n- Any existing GC/cleanup code\n- How workloads are currently managed (create/delete lifecycle)\n- Any relevant configuration or constants\n- Other proposal.md files as examples of format","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288b5e792ffeV8VKHRp1prb0hf (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is my complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis: AgentCube WorkloadManager\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ changes/                    # Change proposals (AR-001 through AR-008)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-001/                 # CRD AgentRuntime type definition\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-002/                 # CRD CodeInterpreter type definition\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-003/                 # CRD shared types and constants\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-004/                 # WorkloadManager HTTP service framework\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-005/                 # Sandbox creation handler\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-006/                 # Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ AR-007/                 # K8s Reconciler controller\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ AR-008/                 # Sandbox GC periodic cleanup (empty skeleton)\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ pkg/\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ apis/runtime/v1alpha1/  # CRD type definitions\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ workloadmanager/        # Core workload management module\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ client-go/                  # Generated Kubernetes client code\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ idle-cleanup/               # Agentd idle cleanup design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ sandbox-orchestration/      # Sandbox orchestration design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ session-routing/            # Session routing design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ session-store/              # Session store design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ code-execution/             # Code execution design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ deployment/                 # Deployment design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ cli-toolkit/                # CLI toolkit design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ python-sdk/                 # Python SDK design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ ci-cd/                      # CI/CD design/spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ integrations/               # Integration spec\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ testing/                    # Testing manifests\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ project.md                  # Project overview\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ design.md                   # Design document (AR-003)\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ go.mod / go.sum             # Go module files\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ delta-spec.md / test_spec.md\n```\n\n**Project Purpose**: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic through session-aware proxies, and manages lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Full Directory Listing of `pkg/workloadmanager`\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ handler/\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ constants.go            # GVRs, labels, annotations, default constants\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ models.go               # Request/response models, SandboxInfo struct\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ sandbox_create.go       # Sandbox creation handler (693 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ sandbox_delete.go       # Sandbox deletion handler (216 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ sandbox_delete_test.go  # Delete handler tests (387 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ sandbox_lifecycle.go    # Lifecycle manager with GC loop (343 lines)\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ sandbox_lifecycle_test.go # Lifecycle tests (696 lines)\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ middleware/                  # (empty directory)\nÔö£ÔöÇÔöÇ reconciler/\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntime reconciliation logic (127 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreter reconciliation logic (105 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ event_handlers.go       # Informer event handlers (165 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ metrics.go              # Prometheus metrics recorder (86 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ pod.go                  # Pod reconciliation logic (100 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ reconciler.go           # Main reconciler struct and Run loop (200 lines)\nÔöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ sync.go                 # Sync handler and workqueue processing (125 lines)\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ types.go                # Interfaces, constants, dependency struct (67 lines)\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ response/\n    Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ response.go             # Unified JSON response helpers (45 lines)\n    ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ response_test.go        # Response tests (110 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Key Types and Interfaces\n\n#### 3.1 CRD Types (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n\n**AgentRuntime** (`agent_type.go`):\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate    // embeds corev1.PodSpec\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration    // default: 15m\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration    // default: 8h\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition\n}\n```\n\n**CodeInterpreter** (`codeinterpreter_types.go`):\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate  // flattened fields\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32              // CodeInterpreter unique\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType        // picod | none\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition\n    Ready      bool\n}\n```\n\n**Shared Types** (`shared_types.go`):\n```go\ntype ProtocolType string    // HTTP | HTTPS\ntype AuthModeType string    // picod | none\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string\n    Name       string\n    Port       uint32\n    Protocol   ProtocolType\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2 WorkloadManager Types\n\n**SandboxReconciler** (`reconciler/reconciler.go`):\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    clientset       clientset.Interface\n    informerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    arLister        listers.AgentRuntimeLister\n    ciLister        listers.CodeInterpreterLister\n    podInformer     coreinformers.PodInformer\n    store           Store\n    workqueue       workqueue.RateLimitingInterface\n    workers         int\n    metricsRecorder MetricsRecorder\n    mu              sync.Mutex\n    running         bool\n    stopCh          chan struct{}\n}\n```\n\n**Store Interface** (`reconciler/types.go`):\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID string) (*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx) (map[string]*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n**MetricsRecorder Interface** (`reconciler/types.go`):\n```go\ntype MetricsRecorder interface {\n    IncReconcileTotal(resourceType, result string)\n    ObserveReconcileDuration(resourceType string, duration time.Duration)\n    IncReconcileErrors(resourceType, errorType string)\n    SetWorkqueueDepth(depth int)\n    IncWorkqueueAdds(resourceType string)\n}\n```\n\n**SandboxInfo** (`handler/models.go`):\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SessionID    string\n    SandboxName  string\n    SandboxID    string\n    WorkloadName string\n    Namespace    string\n    Kind         string       // \"AgentRuntime\" | \"CodeInterpreter\" | \"Sandbox\" | \"SandboxClaim\"\n    PodIP        string\n    EntryPoints  []EntryPoint\n    CreatedAt    time.Time\n    ExpiresAt    time.Time\n    Status       string       // \"pending\" | \"running\" | \"terminated\"\n}\n```\n\n**LifecycleManager** (`handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`):\n```go\ntype LifecycleManager struct {\n    dynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n    store         Store\n    checkInterval time.Duration   // default: 5 minutes\n    defaultTTL    time.Duration   // default: 8 hours\n    stopCh        chan struct{}\n    mu            sync.Mutex\n    running       bool\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing GC / Cleanup Mechanisms\n\nThere are **three layers** of cleanup in the codebase:\n\n#### 4.1 LifecycleManager Timer-Based GC (`handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`)\n\nThis is the **primary existing GC mechanism**:\n\n```go\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) runCleanupLoop(ctx context.Context) {\n    ticker := time.NewTicker(m.checkInterval)  // default: 5 minutes\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return\n        case <-m.stopCh:\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            m.cleanupExpiredSandboxes(ctx)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) cleanupExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context) {\n    sandboxes, _ := m.store.ListSandboxes(ctx)\n    now := time.Now()\n    for _, sb := range sandboxes {\n        if m.isExpired(sb, now) {\n            m.deleteSandbox(ctx, sb)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) isExpired(info *SandboxInfo, now time.Time) bool {\n    if !info.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return !now.Before(info.ExpiresAt)\n    }\n    if !info.CreatedAt.IsZero() {\n        return !now.Before(info.CreatedAt.Add(m.defaultTTL))  // defaultTTL: 8h\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- Ticker interval: **5 minutes** (configurable via `CheckInterval`)\n- Default TTL: **8 hours** (configurable via `DefaultTTL`)\n- Expiration check: Uses `ExpiresAt` if set, otherwise falls back to `CreatedAt + defaultTTL`\n- **No idle-timeout-based cleanup** in this loop (only expiration)\n- Deletes both the CR from the cluster and the entry from the Store\n\n#### 4.2 Reconciler Event-Driven Cleanup (`reconciler/agentruntime.go`, `reconciler/codeinterpreter.go`)\n\nWhen a CR is deleted or enters `Terminated` status, the reconciler immediately cleans up the Store:\n\n```go\n// On DeletionTimestamp set (CR being deleted)\nif ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n    r.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n    return nil\n}\n\n// On status change to Terminated\nif status == StatusTerminated {\n    r.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.3 Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (`idle-cleanup/design.md`)\n\nA separate component (`agentd`) runs as a controller-runtime reconciler that watches Sandbox objects:\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n// Reads annotation \"last-activity-time\" from Sandbox\n// If lastActivity + 15m < now, deletes the Sandbox\n```\n\n**Key constants** (`handler/constants.go`):\n```go\nconst (\n    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8   // hours\n    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15  // minutes\n)\n\nconst (\n    AnnotationIdleTimeout    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n    AnnotationSandboxPodName = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Sandbox/Workload Lifecycle (Create/Delete)\n\n#### 5.1 Creation Flow (`handler/sandbox_create.go`)\n\n**AgentRuntime Sandbox**:\n1. Parse request (`CreateSandboxRequest`: Kind, Name, Namespace)\n2. Lookup AgentRuntime template via informer lister\n3. Generate `sessionID` (UUID) and `sandboxName` (`{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`)\n4. Build Sandbox CR (`agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind `Sandbox`):\n   - Labels: `managed-by`, `session-id`, `workload-name`, `sandbox-name`\n   - Annotations: `idle-timeout` (from `SessionTimeout` or default 15m)\n   - Lifecycle: `shutdownTime = now + TTL` (from `MaxSessionDuration` or default 8h)\n5. `StoreSandbox` (write to Store with status \"pending\")\n6. Register one-time watcher for \"running\" status\n7. Create Sandbox CR via dynamic client\n8. Wait for running (2-minute timeout)\n9. Resolve Pod IP (by name -> annotation -> label selector)\n10. `UpdateSandbox` (update with PodIP, EntryPoints, status \"running\")\n11. Return `CreateSandboxResponse` (SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints)\n12. On failure: rollback (delete created CR)\n\n**CodeInterpreter Sandbox**:\n- If `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Creates `SandboxClaim` (`extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) instead of full Sandbox\n- If `AuthMode == picod`: Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env from Secret\n- Otherwise: Same flow as AgentRuntime\n\n#### 5.2 Deletion Flow (`handler/sandbox_delete.go`)\n\n1. Parse request (SessionID, Namespace)\n2. `Store.GetSandbox(sessionID)` -> 404 if not found\n3. Resolve GVR based on `SandboxInfo.Kind` (Sandbox or SandboxClaim)\n4. Delete CR via dynamic client (NotFound = success, idempotent)\n5. `Store.DeleteSandbox(sessionID)` to clean up Store\n6. Return `DeleteSandboxResponse`\n\n#### 5.3 Reconciler-Driven State Sync\n\nThe `SandboxReconciler` watches AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and Pod resources:\n- **Add**: Store new sandbox entry\n- **Update**: Sync status changes (Pending -> Running -> Terminated)\n- **Delete**: Clean up Store entry\n- **Pod events**: Update PodIP in Store when Pod becomes running\n\n---\n\n### 6. Timer-Based / Cron-Based Mechanisms\n\n| Mechanism | Location | Interval | Purpose |\n|-----------|----------|----------|---------|\n| **LifecycleManager cleanup loop** | `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go:80` | 5 min (configurable) | Delete expired sandboxes (ExpiresAt < now or CreatedAt + TTL) |\n| **Reconciler workqueue rate limiter** | `reconciler/reconciler.go:51` | 5s initial, 5min max | Exponential backoff for failed reconciliations |\n| **Reconciler cache sync timeout** | `reconciler/reconciler.go:159` | 30s | Wait for informer cache sync at startup |\n| **Reconciler shutdown timeout** | `reconciler/reconciler.go:192` | 30s | Force exit if workqueue drain takes too long |\n| **Sandbox creation watcher timeout** | `handler/sandbox_create.go:183` | 2 min | Wait for sandbox to reach \"running\" state |\n| **Sandbox rollback timeout** | `handler/sandbox_create.go:370` | 30s | Delete CR on creation failure |\n| **Sandbox deletion timeout** | `handler/sandbox_delete.go:124` | 30s | Delete CR from cluster |\n| **Agentd idle cleanup** | `idle-cleanup/design.md` | Requeue-based | Delete sandboxes idle > 15 min (reads `last-activity-time` annotation) |\n\n**There is NO cron-based mechanism** -- only `time.NewTicker` and `time.After` are used.\n\n---\n\n### 7. AR-008: Sandbox GC Proposal (Existing Skeleton)\n\nThe existing AR-008 proposal at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-008/proposal.md` is a **bare skeleton** with empty sections:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-008: Sandbox GC Õ«ÜµùÂµ©àþÉåµ£║ÕêÂ\n## µªéÞ┐░: õ©║ AgentCube µ▓Öþ«▒þ╝ûµÄÆþ│╗þ╗ƒÕ«×þÄ░Õ«ÜµùÂÕ×âÕ£¥Õø×µöÂ´╝êGC´╝ëµ£║ÕêÂ\n## Õàâõ┐íµü»: Module: pkg/workloadmanager, Language: Go, Size: S\n## þø«þÜä: (empty)\n## ÞîâÕø┤ - ÕîàÕÉ½: (empty)\n## ÞîâÕø┤ - õ©ìÕîàÕÉ½: (empty)\n## Õ¢▒ÕôìÕêåµ×É: (empty)\n## ÕñçÚÇëµû╣µíê: (empty)\n## Ú¬îµöÂµáçÕçå: (empty)\n## þèÂµÇü: All unchecked\n```\n\nThe `design.md` and `tasks.md` are similarly empty skeletons.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Proposal Format Examples\n\nAll proposals follow this consistent structure (from AR-007, the most complete example):\n\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: Title\n\n## µªéÞ┐░\nBrief summary of the change.\n\n## Õàâõ┐íµü»\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager (or pkg/apis)\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S | M | L\n\n## þø«þÜä\nDetailed explanation of why this change is needed and specific goals (numbered list).\n\n## ÞîâÕø┤\n### ÕîàÕÉ½\nNumbered list of what IS included in scope.\n\n### õ©ìÕîàÕÉ½\nNumbered list of what is NOT included.\n\n## Õ¢▒ÕôìÕêåµ×É\n### þø┤µÄÑÕ¢▒Õôì\n| Component | Impact | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n\n### õ©ïµ©©õ¥ØÞÁû´╝êµ£¼ÕÅÿµø┤Õ«îµêÉÕÉÄÞºúÚöü´╝ë\n| Component | Dependency |\n|---|---|\n\n### µùáÕ¢▒ÕôìþÜäþ╗äõ╗Â\nBullet list of unaffected components.\n\n## ÕñçÚÇëµû╣µíê\n### µû╣µíê A: Name (selected)\nPros and cons.\n### µû╣µíê B: Name (rejected)\nPros, cons, and rejection rationale.\n\n## Ú¬îµöÂµáçÕçå\nNumbered list of acceptance criteria.\n\n## þèÂµÇü\n- [ ] µÅÉµíêÕ«íµƒÑ\n- [ ] Õ«×þÄ░\n- [ ] Ú¬îÞ»ü\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Key Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | Location |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| `DefaultSandboxTTL` | 8 (hours) | `handler/constants.go` |\n| `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` | 15 (minutes) | `handler/constants.go` |\n| `LabelSessionID` | `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id` | `handler/constants.go` |\n| `LabelWorkloadName` | `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name` | `handler/constants.go` |\n| `LabelSandboxName` | `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name` | `handler/constants.go` |\n| `AnnotationIdleTimeout` | `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` | `handler/constants.go` |\n| `maxRetries` | 15 | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `defaultWorkers` | 2 | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `cacheSyncTimeout` | 30s | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `shutdownTimeout` | 30s | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `StatusPending` | `\"pending\"` | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `StatusRunning` | `\"running\"` | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `StatusTerminated` | `\"terminated\"` | `reconciler/types.go` |\n| `SessionExpirationTimeout` (agentd) | 15 minutes | `idle-cleanup/design.md` |\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Observations for GC Implementation\n\n1. **Existing GC is limited**: The `LifecycleManager` only handles expiration-based cleanup (ExpiresAt or CreatedAt+TTL). It does NOT handle idle-timeout-based cleanup.\n\n2. **Two Store interfaces exist**: There is a slight mismatch between `handler.Store` (returns `[]*SandboxInfo`) and `reconciler.Store` (returns `map[string]*SandboxInfo`).\n\n3. **No idle-activity tracking**: The `SandboxInfo` struct has no `LastActivity` or `LastAccessedAt` field, despite the agentd design referencing a `last-activity-time` annotation.\n\n4. **Event-driven cleanup is partial**: The reconciler cleans up the Store when CRs are deleted, but there is no mechanism to clean up orphaned CRs when Store entries are deleted.\n\n5. **AR-008 is empty**: The GC proposal exists but has no content filled in -- it needs to be authored from scratch.\n\n6. **Middleware directory is empty**: The `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/` directory exists but contains no files.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288b5e792ffeV8VKHRp1prb0hf","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore workloadmanager module","time":{"start":1775822837865,"end":1775823066641}}}}
